    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "(Part of https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/39006, https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/22313 read those before commenting here.)\n\n## Problem\n\nUsers need a C toolchain to install treesitter parsers.\n\n## Proposal \n\n- Provide prebuilt parser artifacts from [\"nvim-treeconfig\"](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/39006) CI.\n    - Provide [1 compressed bundle](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/39007#issuecomment-4237657728) of all parsers. So \"installing\" a parser means downloading all the parsers (once) and enabling specific parsers from that bundle.\n- Nvim verifies the checksum when installing a new parser.\n\nNote from https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/22313#issuecomment-1435691063 : \n\n> Shipping all parsers of nvim-treesitter [nvim-treesitter/nvim-treesitter#3688](https://github.com/nvim-treesitter/nvim-treesitter/pull/3688) ~~150 requires 15MB~~. (**Edit:** [outdated](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/39007#issuecomment-4237449661)) Helix ships with all of its parsers in its [release](https://github.com/helix-editor/helix/releases). But parsers will inflate to >100MiB when decompressed (binaries have a very repetitive structure). I had the idea for a long time to have parsers compressed on disk and only decompress when needed\n\n",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "That comment is outdated. Current \"binary\" distribution of nvim-treesitter is 256 Mb on disk. (Also note that parsers depend on `libc`, which means you'll get complaints from people on older distros or musl. Be warned.)",
