            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> What are your thoughts on security, does lux do a checksum?\n\n\nLux stores sha256sums of packages (including pre-built binary rocks) in its lockfile and fails if the source integrity of a package doesn't match what's stored in the lockfile.\n\n> Also what about queries?\n\nFor tree-sitter parsers, we currently embed the queries in the rockspec, see also [our build backend for luarocks](https://github.com/lumen-oss/luarocks-build-treesitter-parser?tab=readme-ov-file#example-rockspec).\nThe pre-built binary rocks are basically zip archives that have the queries and parser bundled.",
